Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of forms I and II of clopidogrel hydrogen sulfate  (CHS) were measured in solvents such as formic acid (FA), N-methylpyrrolidone  (NMP), and N,N-dimethylformamide (DMFA) at a temperature range of (283.15 to  353.15) K. The solubilities of forms I and II of CHS in FA + propan-2-ol, NMP +  propan-2-ol, and DMFA + propan-2-ol were measured at a temperature of 308.15 K  and various propan-2-ol mass fractions. The enthalpy and entropy of dissolution of  CHS forms I and II of CHS in pure solvents were determined by using the van't Hoff  equation.
Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Forms I and II of Clopidogrel Hydrogen Sulfate in Formic  Acid, N-Methylpyrrolidone, and N,N-Dimethylformamide
